23/07/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Serbian Parliament appointed Vladimir Vukcevic to the new post of special prosecutor for war crimes on Tuesday (22 July). The move followed the adoption of a law that set up war crimes tribunals and police investigation units. The prosecutor will head a panel trying low-profile cases. (AP, AFP, B92, Tanjug, Beta, BBC, FoNet - 22/07/03)
